data.enText: a large group of insects, especially bees , moving together in the same direction

data.chText: 一大群蜜蜂 / 蝗虫 / 苍蝇
一大群，一大批（向同方向移动的人）
data.enText: a large group of people, especially when they are all moving quickly in the same direction
to move around in a large group

data.chText: 岛上到处是旅游者熙来攘往。
data.enText: Tourists were swarming all over the island.

before.enText: of bees and other flying insects

data.enText: to move around together in a large group, looking for a place to live
to be full of people or things
The capital city is swarming with police.

means: 一大批(向同方向移动的人)

data.enText: to be full of people or things
The capital city is swarming with police.

tr: a group of many things in the air or on the ground
example: a swarm of insects obscured the light
it discharged a cloud of spores
people were pouring out of the theater
The garden was swarming with bees
The plaza is teeming with undercover policemen

value.def: A swarm of bees or other insects is a large group of them flying together.
value.tran: (蜜蜂等昆虫的)一大群，一大窝

value.def: When bees or other insects swarm, they move or fly in a large group.

example.ex: A dark cloud of bees comes swarming out of the hive.
example.tran: 黑压压的一大群蜜蜂从蜂巢中飞出来。

value.def: When people swarm somewhere, they move there quickly in a large group.

example.ex: People swarmed to the shops, buying up everything in sight.
example.tran: 人们成群地涌向商店，见什么买什么。

value.def: A swarm of people is a large group of them moving about quickly.

example.ex: A swarm of people encircled the hotel...
example.tran: 一大群人围住了这个酒店。

example.ex: Today at the crossing there were swarms of tourists taking photographs.
example.tran: 今天在十字路口有大群的游客在拍照。

value.def: If a place is swarming with people, it is full of people moving about in a busy way.

example.ex: Within minutes the area was swarming with officers who began searching a nearby wood.
example.tran: 几分钟内很多警察就来到了这一地区，开始搜查附近的树林。

value.tran: 挤满，聚集(来来往往的人)
